audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:22:- `/api/session/role-context` only switches among the session's `availableRoleGrants`; it does not mint a new grant.
audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:34:- `#/admin/proof-dashboard` and the canonical proof hierarchy route are route-level entry points, not visible top tabs.
audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:35:- `#/admin/history` is a hidden-records workspace, but admin search can still surface requests from that section.
audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:36:- Academic role options in the teaching portal are derived from the current bootstrap snapshot, so proof scope can hide roles that still exist in the underlying session.
audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:40:- The academic UI derives `allowedRoles` from the proof-scoped bootstrap, while `/api/session/role-context` uses the underlying session grants. That can make a role appear unavailable in the UI even when it is still switchable.
audit-map/15-final-maps/role-feature-matrix.md:48:- The live proof-scoped bootstrap may hide some active session grants in the UI, but the session still retains them; the full impact on role switching is only partially verified.
