@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@
+# Feature Template v1.0
+
+- Feature name: Public portal chooser and hash routing
+- Parent domain: Bootstrap / portal entry
+- Roles: Public / unauthenticated, academic faculty, SYSTEM_ADMIN
+- Intent: Let a visitor choose the academic or system-admin portal from the root chooser, and keep portal selection stable through hash-based routing.
+- Source files: [`src/App.tsx`](../../src/App.tsx), [`src/portal-entry.tsx`](../../src/portal-entry.tsx), [`src/portal-routing.ts`](../../src/portal-routing.ts)
+- Entry points: `PortalRouterApp`, `PortalEntryScreen`, `resolvePortalRoute()`, `navigateToPortal()`, `clearPortalWorkspaceHints()`
+- Routes: `#/`, `#/app`, `#/admin`
+- Panels/cards/modals/tabs involved: Academic portal card, system-admin portal card, theme toggle
+- Atomic user actions:
+  - Open the root chooser at `#/`
+  - Toggle the portal theme
+  - Click the academic portal card
+  - Click the system-admin portal card
+- Automatic/system actions:
+  - Normalize the current hash into `home`, `app`, or `admin`
+  - Persist theme mode in localStorage
+  - Clear remembered academic/admin workspace hints when leaving the portal
+  - Mount the matching runtime shell for the selected portal
+- API/backend calls: None
+- State dependencies: `window.location.hash`, localStorage theme mode, remembered workspace hint keys
+- Persistence dependencies: `AIRMENTOR_STORAGE_KEYS.themeMode`, `AIRMENTOR_STORAGE_KEYS.currentFacultyId`, `AIRMENTOR_STORAGE_KEYS.currentAdminFacultyId`
+- Permissions/scope logic: None at chooser level; the chosen portal determines the next auth boundary.
+- Expected behavior: The chooser renders both portals, `#/app` resolves to the academic shell, `#/admin` resolves to the sysadmin shell, and subroutes remain within the chosen portal bucket.
+- Empty/loading/error states: No remote data is fetched; SSR or `window` absence falls back to normalized theme defaults; no explicit error UI is shown here.
+- Data read: Hash route, theme mode, portal hint keys
+- Data written: Hash route, theme mode, cleared workspace hints
+- Downstream effects: Enters `OperationalApp` or `SystemAdminApp` and prevents stale faculty identifiers from leaking across portal boundaries.
+- Hidden couplings: The portal exit path and workspace reset both depend on shared localStorage keys from `repositories`.
+- Live behavior notes: The Pages root is live and the chooser is the first split before any backend auth; route parsing coverage was verified locally in `tests/portal-routing.test.ts`.
+- Tests covering it: [`tests/portal-routing.test.ts`](../../tests/portal-routing.test.ts)
+- Known gaps: No dedicated browser E2E yet exercises the actual card clicks or theme persistence.
+- Open questions: None.
+- Confidence level: High
+
